"Sigmundsson F., Pinel V., Lund B., Albino F., Pagli C., Geirsson H., Sturkell E.","Climate effects on volcanism: Influence on magmatic systems of loading and unloading from ice mass variations, with examples from Iceland",2010,"Philosophical Transactions of the Royal Society A: Mathematical, Physical and Engineering Sciences","368","1919",,"2519","2534",,,10.1098/rsta.2010.0042,"http://www.scopus.com/inward/record.url?eid=2-s2.0-77952997062&partnerID=40&md5=b38a61e7aff8fcc7f6e1313f6416da8b","Nordic Volcanological Center, Institute of Earth Sciences, University of Iceland, 101 Reykjavik, Iceland; Laboratoire de Géophysique Interne et Tectonophysique, Université de Savoie, Campus Scientifique, 73376 Le Bourget-du-Lac Cedex, France; Department of Earth Sciences, Uppsala University, Villavdgen 16, 752 36 Uppsala, Sweden; School of Earth and Environment, Maths/Earth and Environment Building, University of Leeds, Leeds LS2 9JT, United Kingdom; Physics Department, Icelandic Meteorological Office, 150 Reykjavik, Iceland; Department of Earth Sciences, Faculty of Science, University of Gothenburg, PO Box 460, 405, 30 Gothenburg, Sweden","Sigmundsson, F., Nordic Volcanological Center, Institute of Earth Sciences, University of Iceland, 101 Reykjavik, Iceland; Pinel, V., Laboratoire de Géophysique Interne et Tectonophysique, Université de Savoie, Campus Scientifique, 73376 Le Bourget-du-Lac Cedex, France; Lund, B., Department of Earth Sciences, Uppsala University, Villavdgen 16, 752 36 Uppsala, Sweden; Albino, F., Laboratoire de Géophysique Interne et Tectonophysique, Université de Savoie, Campus Scientifique, 73376 Le Bourget-du-Lac Cedex, France; Pagli, C., School of Earth and Environment, Maths/Earth and Environment Building, University of Leeds, Leeds LS2 9JT, United Kingdom; Geirsson, H., Physics Department, Icelandic Meteorological Office, 150 Reykjavik, Iceland; Sturkell, E., Department of Earth Sciences, Faculty of Science, University of Gothenburg, PO Box 460, 405, 30 Gothenburg, Sweden","Pressure influences both magma production and the failure of magma chambers. Changes in pressure interact with the local tectonic settings and can affect magmatic activity. Present-day reduction in ice load on subglacial volcanoes due to global warming is modifying pressure conditions in magmatic systems. The large pulse in volcanic production at the end of the last glaciation in Iceland suggests a link between unloading and volcanism, and models of that process can help to evaluate future scenarios. A viscoelastic model of glacio-isostatic adjustment that considers melt generation demonstrates how surface unloading may lead to a pulse in magmatic activity. Iceland's ice caps have been thinning since 1890 and glacial rebound at rates exceeding 20mmysup-1/sup is ongoing. Modelling predicts a significant amount of 'additional' magma generation under Iceland due to ice retreat. The unloading also influences stress conditions in shallow magma chambers, modifying their failure conditions in a manner that depends critically on ice retreat, the shape and depth of magma chambers as well as the compressibility of the magma. An annual cycle of land elevation in iceland, due to seasonal variation of ice mass, indicates an annual modulation of failure conditions in subglacial magma chambers. Copyright © 2010 The Royal Society.","Glacial rebound; Global warming; Ice retreat; Magma; Pressure; Volcanoes","Annual cycle; Climate effects; Failure conditions; Glacial rebound; Ice loads; Ice mass; Ice-caps; Icelands; Loading and unloading; Magma; Magma chamber; Magma generation; Magma pressure; Magmatic activity; Magmatic systems; Pressure conditions; Seasonal variation; Stress condition; Tectonic settings; Viscoelastic models; Glacial geology; Global warming; Unloading; Volcanoes; Ice",,,,,,"Albino, F., Pinel, V., Sigmundsson, F., Influence of surface load variations on eruption likelihood: Application to two icelandic subglacial volcanoes, gńmsvötn and Katla. Geophys. J. Int.; Árnadóttir, T., Lund, B., Jiang, W., Geirsson, G., Björnsson, H., Einarsson, P., Sigurdsson, T., Glacial rebound and plate spreading: Results from the first countrywide GPS observations in Iceland (2009) Geophys. J. Int., 177, pp. 691-716. , doi:10.1111/j.1365-246X.2008.04059.x; Davis, R.O., Selvadurai, A.P.S., (2001) Elasticity and Geomechanics, , Cambridge, UK: Cambridge University Press; Eliasson, J., Larsen, G., Gudmundsson, M.T., Sigmundsson, F., Probabilistic model for eruptions and associated flood events in the Katla caldera, Iceland (2006) Comput. Geosci., 10, pp. 179-200; Grapenthin, R., Sigmundsson, F., Geirsson, H., Arnadottir, T., Pinel, V., Icelandic rhythmics: Annual modulation of land elevation and plate spreading by snow load (2006) Geophysical Research Letters, 33 (24), pp. L24305. , DOI 10.1029/2006GL028081; Gudmundsson, M.T., Höganadóttir, P., Kristinsson, A.B., Gudbjornsson, S., Geothermal activity in the subglacial Katla caldera, Iceland, 1999-2005, studied with radar altimetry (2007) Ann. Glaciol., 45, pp. 66-72. , doi:10.3189/172756407782282444; Ito, G., Reykjanes 'V'-shaped ridges originating from a pulsing and dehydrating mantle plume (2001) Nature, 411 (6838), pp. 681-684. , DOI 10.1038/35079561; Jull, M., McKenzie, D., The effect of deglaciation on mantle melting beneath Iceland (1996) J. Geophys. Res., 101 (21), p. 828. , doi:10.1029/96JB01308; Lund, B., Näslund, J.-O., Glacial isostatic adjustment: Implications for glacially induced faulting and nuclear waste repositories (2009) Volcanic and Tectonic Hazard Assessment for Nuclear Facilities, , (eds C. B. Connor, N. A. Chapman & L. J. Connor). Cambridge, UK: Cambridge University Press; Lund, B., Pagli, C., Sigmundsson, F., Schmidt, P., Árnadóttir, Th., Björnsson, H., Geirsson, H., Sturkell, E., Estimating the effects of current deglaciation in Iceland on earthquake occurrence and volcanism (2009) Eos, Trans. AGU, 90, p. 52. , Fall Meet. Suppl., Abstract G53B-0673; MacLenn